results.name: Numbers k such that there are exactly 6 numbers j for which binomial(k, floor(k/2)) / binomial(k,j) is an integer, i.e., A080383(k) = 6.
link: Vaclav Kotesovec, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..44084
example: For n=9, the central binomial coefficient (C(9,4) = 126) is divisible by C(9,0), C(9,1), C(9,4), C(9,5), C(9,8), and C(9,9); certain primes are missing, certain composites are here.
program: (PARI) isok(n) = my(b=binomial(n, n\2)); sum(i=0, n, (b % binomial(n, i)) == 0) == 6; \\ _Michel Marcus_, Jul 29 2017
results.author: _Labos Elemer_, Mar 12 2003
